      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/30/12",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلَ رَجُلٌ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَللُّقَطَةِ وَ أَنَا أَسْمَعُ فَقَالَ \"تُعَرِّفُهَا سَنَةً فَإِنْ وَجَدْتَ صَاحِبَهَا وَ إِلاَّ فَأَنْتَ أَحَقُّ بِهَا\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4058 - It is narrated from Hanan ibn Sadir, who said: A man asked Abu Abdullah (as) about lost property while I was listening.\nImam (as) said: \"Announce it for one year. If you find its owner, return it to him; otherwise, you are more entitled to keep it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
